                seal or a thermostat, might only take an hour or two, leading to
                lower labor costs. More complex issues, like fixing a
                malfunctioning compressor or repairing the electronic control
                board, can be time-consuming and require specialized skills,
                thereby increasing labor costs. Typically, you might see labor
                costs ranging from $100 to $300 for straightforward repairs and
                $300 to $500 or more for more complicated issues.
