          <div class="content__page-full-desc">
            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Compressor Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer is not cooling, making loud noises, or cycling too
                frequently. The compressor is essential for the cooling cycle,
                pumping refrigerant through the coils. It's one of the most
                expensive parts to replace.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Evaporator Fan Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer is cool but not cold enough, or there's uneven
                cooling, with frost building up in some areas more than others.
                This fan circulates cold air throughout the freezer. If it
                fails, the freezer may not maintain the desired temperature.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Thermostat Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer does not maintain the set temperature, run
                continuously, or not run at all. The thermostat monitors and
                regulates the temperature inside the freezer.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Defrost Heater Issues</h3>
              <p>
                There is excessive frost buildup inside the freezer compartment.
                The defrost heater prevents ice from accumulating on the
                freezerâ€™s evaporator coils by melting the frost during the
                defrost cycle.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Door Seal (Gasket) Issues</h3>
              <p>
                Frost buildup near the door, energy waste, or a constantly
                running freezer are signs of a faulty door seal, which can leak
                cold air, reducing efficiency and effectiveness.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Start Relay Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer is not starting, has intermittent operation, or
                makes clicking sounds. The start relay helps the compressor
                begin operating. A faulty relay can prevent the freezer from
                cooling.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Control Board Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer is not functioning correctly, has erratic behaviors,
                or has nonresponsive electronic components. The control board
                governs the major electrical functions of the freezer. If it
                fails, it can affect many aspects of its operation.
              </p>

              <h3>Freezer Temperature Sensor or Thermistor Issues</h3>
              <p>
                The freezer is not maintaining the correct temperature or
                temperature fluctuations. This sensor monitors the internal
                temperature and signals the control board to adjust cooling.
              </p>
